      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09D\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table entries into table `J09D_temp` only for tours that start with `J09D`.\\n\\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09D_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `J09D_temp`:\\n   - if a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`\\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`\\n\\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09D`.\\n   Use these exact column names in the export:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the exported CSV file attached.\\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\\n\\n\"}",
            "id": "lc_d1fe03fb-f451-4108-9ea5-0bae2105ed1d"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "e470e04f-e9f1-45a5-9106-228ff8fa6958",
        "tool_call_id": "call_wEVPBtDd07FUVlF21kDKeR7I",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09D",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table entries into table `J09D_temp` only for tours that start with `J09D`.\n\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09D_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `J09D_temp`:\n   - if a `HAUS` has fewer than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`\n\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09D`.\n   Use these exact column names in the export:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the exported CSV file attached.\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n10. Delete the temporary table.\n\n"
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
